parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to continue running even after the key is removed, leading to a potential safety hazard, as the vehicle may move unexpectedly, and the driver may lose control.
symptoms: The key starts rotating in the ignition while driving
the engine does not shut off when the key is removed
the vehicle continues to run even after the key is taken out of the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system to disengage when the brakes are applied can lead to unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control does not disengage when the brakes are applied
the vehicle does not decelerate when expected

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Popping Out of 1st Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or popping out of 1st gear can cause loss of power, reduced acceleration, and increased risk of accidents, especially when merging onto highways or navigating uphill.
symptoms: The transmission suddenly slips or pops out of 1st gear while accelerating
